          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-19 10:19:23" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an extended meaning of {L:Ἑλληνίς&lt;SDBG:Ἑλληνίς:000000&gt;}[a] ‘Greek woman,’ {D:11.91}) a female who is a Gentile in view of being a Greek</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>Gentile woman</Gloss>
                <Gloss>non-Jew</Gloss>
                <Gloss>Greek</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though one may translate Ἑλληνίς in {S:04401701200018} as ‘Greek,’ the focus is probably upon these women as being Gentiles rather than merely Greeks, for it is the Gentile status of these persons which seems to have been particularly aggravating to some of the Jews in that region.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
